cs.PL, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the trade-offs between low-level system programming and higher-level capability in programming languages, which is a topic typically covered in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on resource-scarce embedded smart devices, which falls under the Embedded Systems (cs.EM) sub-category. The paper also discusses the control over resources consumed by the run-time executive, which is a topic covered in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper proposes a system of light-weighted and modular extensions, which is a topic covered in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the design goals and trade-offs, which is a topic covered in the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
